'''Hans''' is the servant of [[Duke Horacio]]{{CitePostbag |issue=4 |author=Duke Horacio |letter=3 }} and can be found walking in circles around the [[Lumbridge Castle]] courtyard. He is easily scared, screaming and running away in fright when threatened.{{CitePostbag |issue=2 |author=Hans |letter=2 }} He can tell players how old their accounts are or how long they've spent online by talking to him.

Hans can also be spoken to by selecting "random contact" on the [[NPC Contact]] spell. If Hans is contacted, your character will claim you are a knight coming to kill everyone in Lumbridge Castle. Hans panics in response.

==Treasure Trails==
*{{CrypticNPC|Hans|beginner|Always walking around the castle grounds and somehow knows everyone's age.}}
*{{CrypticNPC|Hans|easy|Speak to Hans to solve the clue.}}
*{{Anagram|Hans|medium|SNAH}}.
*{{CrypticNPC|Hans|hard|Snah? I feel all confused, like one of those cakes...}}

==Holiday events==
* He played a minor role in the [[2016 Birthday event]], where he witnessed a seagull take a [[gnome child]]'s [[hat]]. 
* In the [[2018 Christmas event]], where he was one of the recipients of a gift from Duke Horacio. He is given a [[chair]] from the Duke's room, which he takes in relief, having spent many years circling the castle without relief.{{CiteNPC |npc=Hans |quote=Oh my aching feet! A chair! Just what I've been needing! I'm going to go sit by the fountain, so pretty this time of year. |loc=2018 Christmas event }}{{CiteNPC |npc=Account{{!}}Player character |quote=I reckon Hans could do with a sit down as he's always on his feet. |loc=2018 Christmas event }}
* In the [[20th Anniversary event]], he gives his navigational chart to the gnome child to help the latter return to the [[Realm of Memories]].
* In the [[2022 Birthday event]], he was one of the participants in the cook off hosted by [[My Arm]].

